</div></article><div class="item-page"><article class="art-post"><div class="art-postcontent clearfix"><div class="art-article"><h1><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em><strong>GUNSMITH SERVICES </strong></em></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><em><strong>(Licensed FFL</strong></em><em><strong>, Pr</strong></em><em><strong>ofessional Gunsmith)</strong></em></span></h1>
<p><strong><em> Effective June 15, 2013</em><br /> </strong><em>Prices subject to change without notice</em></p>
<h2><em><span style="color: #ffcc00;">Completion Time</span></em></h2>
<p>Sight Installation 2 to 5 days (longer if machining is required)<br />General Repairs 10-15 days./ Machine work 30-60 days/ Plus Parts shipping times depend on vendors. <br /> Coatings Average time for 2013, 10-15 Business days rarely over 30 days max. (some projects due to complexity, material retention etc. can take up to 60 days)<br /><br /><em><span style="color: #ffcc00;">Minimum Charge:</span></em><br /> Per Firearm $25 (no exceptions)<br />Shop Rate: $65 per hour<br /> Per Hour $85 (for all custom gunsmith &amp; machining services not listed)<br /><br /><em><span style="color: #ffcc00;">Exclusions:</span></em><br /> We reserve the right to refuse <span style="color: #ffcc00;">work deemed to be unsafe. We DO NOT remove or deactivate firearm safeties.</span> If test firing a firearm is requested or required, the test fire is performed using commercially loaded factory ammunition at additional cost (Thanks for understanding). We DO NOT perform test fires with hand loaded ammunition or surplus military ammunition. Parts affixed with epoxy or high strength Loctite will incur an additional charge.</p>
<p><em><span style="color: #ffcc00;">Shop Supplies:</span></em>Moderate charges (5% of ticket) apply to cover disposable expenses required to perform,maintain,equipment,supplies, chemicals etc.</p>
